#### 4. Remove Unnecessary Files

```bash
cd /opt/civilx-website

# Remove excluded files from backend
cd backend
rm -rf storage/ data/ *.log venv/ __pycache__/ .env* cache/

# Remove excluded files from frontend
cd ../universe/universe
rm -rf node_modules/ .next/ .env* *.log
```

#### 5. Initialize Git Repository

```bash
cd /opt/civilx-website

# Initialize Git
git init

# Configure Git user
git config user.name "CivilX Server"
git config user.email "server@civilx.ru"

# Rename branch to main
git branch -M main
```

#### 6. Add Remote and Configure Authentication

```bash
# Add remote
git remote add origin https://github.com/F1bonacci66/civilx.univers.git

# Configure credential helper
git config --global credential.helper store

# Store GitHub token (replace with your token)
echo "https://YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN@github.com" > ~/.git-credentials
```

**Note**: Replace `YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN` with your actual GitHub Personal Access Token. The token should have `repo` scope.

#### 7. Add Files and Create Commit

```bash
cd /opt/civilx-website

# Add all files
git add .

# Create commit with current date
DATE=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)
git commit -m "chore: сохранение актуальной версии с сервера $DATE"
```

#### 8. Push to GitHub

```bash
# Push to main branch
git push https://YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN@github.com/F1bonacci66/civilx.univers.git main
```

**Alternative using stored credentials:**
```bash
git push origin main
```

